&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(217, 94, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Technical Analyst in &lt;strong&gt;Madrid, Seville, Milan or London&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role plays a critical role in safeguarding and optimizing the technical performance of WiseEnergy’s global solar PV portfolio. This position is responsible for ensuring high levels of asset availability and strong performance ratios across all sites, while proactively identifying and resolving technical issues that may impact operations. Acting as a key technical reference, the role bridges operational performance with strategic objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;In close collaboration with O&amp;amp;M contractors and internal stakeholders, the Senior Technical Analyst oversees technical operations, ensures compliance with contractual and regulatory requirements, and serves as the primary technical interface with clients. Through effective coordination of site activities, reporting, and technical documentation, this role ensures the highest standards of operational excellence across the portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Beyond day-to-day operations, the role contributes to continuous improvement and long-term business success. By mentoring junior analysts, driving process optimization, and strengthening technical capabilities within the team, the Senior Technical Analyst directly supports WiseEnergy’s mission to maximize asset value and deliver reliable, sustainable energy solutions across the global renewable energy market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
