&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(217, 94, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WiseEnergy is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Technical Analyst &amp;amp; Site Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to oversee the technical performance, operational reliability, and field activities of a portfolio of utility-scale solar PV assets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid role combining technical asset analysis with hands-on site management. The successful candidate will be responsible for monitoring plant performance, managing technical incidents, coordinating O&amp;amp;M contractors, conducting site inspections, and ensuring compliance with contractual, regulatory, and safety requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Acting as the key technical representative for assigned assets, you will work closely with internal teams, clients, contractors, and stakeholders to maximize asset availability, optimize performance, and drive continuous improvement across the portfolio. This role offers a unique opportunity to contribute directly to the growth and operational excellence of renewable energy projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(217, 94, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor, analyze, and report on the daily technical and operational performance of utility-scale solar PV plants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify performance trends, diagnose technical issues, and implement corrective actions to maximize energy production, plant availability, and performance ratios.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage technical incidents from identification through resolution, ensuring minimal operational impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary technical interface between WiseEnergy, O&amp;amp;M contractors, EPC contractors, clients, and other stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular site visits and inspections to assess asset condition, maintenance quality, operational effectiveness, HSE compliance, and technical risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee contractor performance and ensure compliance with contractual obligations, KPIs, and industry best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and deliver technical performance reports, operational analyses, and annual O&amp;amp;M budgets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce site inspection and risk-based reports, prioritizing actions according to generation impact, operational risk, safety, and compliance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support EPC punch-list management and monitor EPC warranty obligations during post-construction phases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Distribution Network Operators (DNOs), insurers, regulatory bodies, and external stakeholders to ensure ongoing compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate technical documentation, asset records, and operational procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support SCADA monitoring, troubleshooting activities, and system integration projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in technical due diligence, feasibility assessments, and the evaluation of new renewable energy opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support engineering activities during construction, commissioning, and operational phases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct technical audits and contribute to business continuity and disaster recovery planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive process improvements, strengthen internal controls, and support operational excellence initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior team members and contribute to the development of technical best practices across the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
